WEBVTT

00:00.478 --> 00:02.915
[Ruggieri] Previously
onThe Serpent Queen...

00:03.003 --> 00:04.352
[crowd exclaiming]

00:04.482 --> 00:06.658
Madame de Poitiers,
the king is dead.

00:06.789 --> 00:09.922
I will wind her up
and watch that silly girl

00:10.053 --> 00:12.316
burn this country
to the ground.

00:12.403 --> 00:13.883
My first order of business--

00:14.014 --> 00:15.189
A decree that makes
Protestantism illegal

00:15.319 --> 00:16.364
on French soil.

00:16.494 --> 00:18.366
-Fuck off.
-Banishment.

00:18.496 --> 00:20.455
You bitch. You fucking bitch.

00:20.585 --> 00:22.326
[grunting]

00:22.457 --> 00:23.936
Our niece
is out of fucking control.

00:24.067 --> 00:25.286
Do you have a plan?

00:25.416 --> 00:26.896
Separate the king
from Mary's influence.

00:27.027 --> 00:28.637
[tense music plays]

00:28.767 --> 00:30.247
I must ask you to reconsider

00:30.334 --> 00:31.770
before we reach
our destination.

00:31.901 --> 00:33.381
Or what happens
at our destination, Mother?

00:33.511 --> 00:34.686
I just don't want
to see anything happen to you.

00:34.817 --> 00:36.688
-That's all.
-[coughing]

00:36.819 --> 00:38.560
[Mary] Help, help, help!

00:38.690 --> 00:39.909
I believe Catherine

00:40.040 --> 00:42.085
was responsible
for what happened.

00:42.216 --> 00:44.305
I wrote to my cousin
in England asking for help.

00:44.435 --> 00:46.829
I believe Catherine
has intercepted

00:46.959 --> 00:48.396
her letter in return.

00:48.483 --> 00:50.572
It would be my honor

00:50.702 --> 00:52.443
to help you rid France
of the Serpent Queen.

00:52.574 --> 00:53.749
Good.

00:56.665 --> 00:59.407
[dramatic music plays]

00:59.581 --> 01:02.323
♪ ♪

01:20.254 --> 01:23.213
[birds chirping]

01:23.344 --> 01:26.086
[tense music plays]

01:26.260 --> 01:29.045
♪ ♪

01:39.229 --> 01:40.187
[gasps]

01:40.317 --> 01:44.234
[whimpering]

01:44.365 --> 01:48.195
[chuckles]
Are you looking for me, hm?

01:48.369 --> 01:49.979
♪ ♪

01:50.110 --> 01:52.764
Apparently,
I'm not the only one.

01:52.895 --> 01:54.244
I presume you're the one

01:54.375 --> 01:55.811
who told Mary
where her men could find me.

01:57.595 --> 01:59.815
Catherine did not
leave me much choice.

01:59.989 --> 02:01.556
♪ ♪

02:01.686 --> 02:03.601
No, no, she's good at that.

02:03.775 --> 02:06.561
♪ ♪

02:08.432 --> 02:10.391
Is this what you're here for?

02:11.783 --> 02:13.045
Do you know what it is?

02:13.133 --> 02:16.005
♪ ♪

02:16.136 --> 02:17.920
Queen Elizabeth's seal.

02:18.050 --> 02:20.140
Or a rough approximation of it,
yeah.

02:22.098 --> 02:24.927
Now all you have to do

02:25.057 --> 02:27.538
is decide what you're
gonna do with it, hm?

02:27.712 --> 02:30.454
♪ ♪

02:40.551 --> 02:42.249
You wanted to see me?

02:46.470 --> 02:49.212
You've been listening
to my story for a few days now.

02:51.867 --> 02:54.174
Would you like
to know how it ends?

02:55.784 --> 02:58.134
I would.

02:58.265 --> 03:00.745
But perhaps I should
be the one to tell you.

03:03.400 --> 03:06.838
That was the plan, was it not?

03:09.058 --> 03:11.800
Go on then.

03:11.930 --> 03:13.541
I'm listening.

03:13.628 --> 03:16.108
[tense music plays]

03:16.239 --> 03:18.415
[Rahima] You convinced
Montmorency and the Bourbons

03:18.546 --> 03:20.156
to join your kidnapping plot.

03:20.330 --> 03:23.115
♪ ♪

03:23.899 --> 03:25.770
[coughing]

03:25.901 --> 03:26.902
[Rahima] Though you
may have regretted it

03:27.032 --> 03:28.991
almost immediately.

03:29.078 --> 03:31.211
[Mary] Francis, oh, my--please!

03:31.341 --> 03:33.125
I didn't think he was ill.

03:33.256 --> 03:34.301
-Francis.
-[Mary] Please, help me!

03:34.431 --> 03:36.303
[gasping]

03:36.390 --> 03:37.739
-[Mary] Help, help, help!
-Stop the carriage!

03:37.869 --> 03:39.393
Stop!

03:39.523 --> 03:41.221
[person] Stop now!

03:41.351 --> 03:42.309
Hold!

03:42.396 --> 03:45.399
♪ ♪

03:45.529 --> 03:47.314
Hold the carriage!

03:47.444 --> 03:49.011
Why are they stopping there?

03:49.141 --> 03:50.404
How the fuck should I know?

03:50.578 --> 03:53.755
♪ ♪

03:54.495 --> 03:56.192
[Mary]
Someone help him, please!

03:56.323 --> 03:57.976
Mary--[coughing]

03:58.107 --> 03:59.369
[person] What's going on?

03:59.543 --> 04:02.677
♪ ♪

04:02.807 --> 04:04.374
[Mary] Help, help, help.
Please!

04:04.505 --> 04:05.332
[Rahima]
So you devised another plan...

04:05.462 --> 04:06.768
Help me!

04:06.898 --> 04:07.769
[Rahima]
A plan that would help you

04:07.856 --> 04:09.249
assume a power

04:09.379 --> 04:10.728
you always knew
should be yours...

04:10.859 --> 04:11.990
What's she doing?

04:12.121 --> 04:13.731
[Rahima] And yours alone.

04:14.166 --> 04:15.646
An attack on the king!

04:15.777 --> 04:16.647
[arrow whistling]

04:16.778 --> 04:18.127
[groans]

04:18.258 --> 04:19.824
[people shouting]

04:19.955 --> 04:22.566
Surround the king!

04:22.697 --> 04:23.480
[Catherine] Get down!

04:23.611 --> 04:25.613
[Francis gasping]

04:25.743 --> 04:27.528
Stay with the carriage!

04:27.615 --> 04:30.574
[people shouting]

04:30.705 --> 04:31.967
[dramatic music plays]

04:32.054 --> 04:33.185
It's okay, it's okay.

04:33.273 --> 04:36.058
♪ ♪

04:38.147 --> 04:39.627
Fuck this.

04:39.801 --> 04:42.543
♪ ♪

04:52.727 --> 04:53.554
[horse neighs]

04:53.728 --> 04:56.470
♪ ♪

05:09.613 --> 05:11.876
Francis, please.

05:12.007 --> 05:14.139
Don't leave me alone
in this wicked, godless world.

05:14.270 --> 05:15.880
-Please!
-[swords clanging]

05:16.011 --> 05:17.229
Ahh!

05:17.404 --> 05:20.189
♪ ♪

05:20.320 --> 05:23.235
Fuck, fuck, fuck. Fuck.

05:23.323 --> 05:26.151
♪ ♪

05:28.328 --> 05:29.241
-[horse neighs]
-[swords clash]

05:36.118 --> 05:37.728
[breathing shakily]

05:37.859 --> 05:39.513
You?

05:39.600 --> 05:40.992
[tense music plays]

05:41.079 --> 05:43.734
-[horse neighs]
-[groaning]

05:43.908 --> 05:47.216
♪ ♪

05:48.086 --> 05:50.567
No, no, no, no,
you... you misunderstand.

05:50.654 --> 05:53.309
Un-fucking-believable.

05:53.440 --> 05:55.180
I was- I was here to protect the
king.

05:55.311 --> 05:56.921
I... I'd heard rumors
of a plot.

05:57.052 --> 05:59.663
Oh, so that's why
you're in a wood,

05:59.794 --> 06:01.926
hiding underneath a log?

06:02.057 --> 06:04.494
-Yeah.
-Mm.

06:04.625 --> 06:06.017
You're so fucked.

06:06.148 --> 06:08.846
[solemn music plays]

06:09.020 --> 06:11.806
♪ ♪

06:14.678 --> 06:16.550
[guard] The attack is over!

06:16.680 --> 06:19.770
[Francis groaning]

06:19.857 --> 06:21.946
It's okay, it's okay,
it's okay.

06:22.120 --> 06:24.775
♪ ♪

06:27.125 --> 06:30.041
[suspenseful music plays]

06:30.172 --> 06:31.826
What are you doing?

06:31.956 --> 06:33.305
I don't know what the fuck
you're playing at,

06:33.436 --> 06:35.003
but if he talks, Mary
won't leave a head in place.

06:35.090 --> 06:37.309
I won't say anything,
not a word, I swear.

06:37.440 --> 06:38.833
Antoine,
I've known you all your life,

06:38.963 --> 06:41.183
and you stand
for absolutely nothing.

06:41.313 --> 06:42.532
I can't trust you.

06:42.663 --> 06:44.273
Sorry about that.

06:44.404 --> 06:45.927
-He is the regent!
-I don't give a shit who he is.

06:46.101 --> 06:48.886
♪ ♪

06:57.460 --> 06:58.679
What the fuck is happening?

06:59.984 --> 07:02.944
[Montmorency groaning]

07:03.031 --> 07:05.337
Antoine, you must run.

07:05.468 --> 07:06.861
Follow the creek,
and in a few miles,

07:06.991 --> 07:08.340
you will find a farmhouse.

07:08.471 --> 07:09.254
I will send someone for you.

07:09.385 --> 07:10.647
You will be safe there.

07:10.734 --> 07:12.997
Antoine, do you want to die?

07:13.128 --> 07:14.172
Run!

07:14.259 --> 07:17.262
♪ ♪

07:17.393 --> 07:19.090
Please forgive me.

07:19.221 --> 07:21.919
[somber music plays]

07:22.093 --> 07:24.835
♪ ♪

07:31.276 --> 07:32.103
What happened?

07:33.453 --> 07:34.366
It was Antoine.

07:35.411 --> 07:36.804
Antoine?

07:36.934 --> 07:38.893
Didn't think he had it in him.

07:39.023 --> 07:40.851
He's still breathing. Guard!

07:40.982 --> 07:42.505
-[guard] Yes, sir.
-Get help!

07:42.636 --> 07:43.811
Take the constable
to the hospital,

07:43.898 --> 07:44.855
and make sure
he's well-guarded!

07:44.942 --> 07:45.987
[guard] Right away, sir.

07:46.117 --> 07:48.859
[tense music plays]

07:49.033 --> 07:52.384
♪ ♪

07:52.950 --> 07:54.125
We will bring the dogs
and hunt him down.

07:55.997 --> 07:58.086
I wouldn't worry.

07:58.216 --> 08:00.262
It's Antoine, he won't get far.

08:00.392 --> 08:01.481
You wouldn't worry?

08:04.048 --> 08:06.137
Do you have any idea
what just happened?

08:07.182 --> 08:09.271
If my idiot cousins think
they can get away with this,

08:09.401 --> 08:11.229
we're closer to civil war
than any of us imagined.

08:12.883 --> 08:15.625
We need to find Antoine
and kill him

08:15.756 --> 08:17.497
before he raises an army
of pissed off Protestants.

08:18.367 --> 08:19.586
Of course.

08:24.329 --> 08:26.984
[Mary crying softly]

08:27.071 --> 08:29.160
Is it possible that this
is God's plan for me...

08:31.728 --> 08:33.513
...when I am yet so young?

08:33.643 --> 08:37.734
Niece, whatever
His divine plan may be,

08:37.865 --> 08:40.084
you can always turn to me,
as God's representative,

08:40.171 --> 08:41.651
for comfort and guidance.

08:41.782 --> 08:43.697
Yes, Mary,
take comfort in the church,

08:43.784 --> 08:46.351
and leave governance to us,
your uncles.

08:46.482 --> 08:48.745
We have your best interests
at heart.

08:48.832 --> 08:50.442
But my faith
and my governance are one.

08:50.573 --> 08:53.097
Yes, up until this moment.

08:53.228 --> 08:54.925
But the thing is,
the Bourbons would never

08:55.012 --> 08:56.840
have attempted
something like this

08:56.927 --> 08:59.408
if they did not believe they
had the support of the people.

08:59.539 --> 09:00.757
There is widespread discontent

09:00.844 --> 09:03.064
with these
anti-Protestant policies.

09:03.194 --> 09:04.500
I have heard there are critics

09:04.631 --> 09:05.545
even in the king's
personal bodyguard.

09:06.676 --> 09:07.634
The king's men?

09:08.635 --> 09:09.592
Turn against him?

09:09.723 --> 09:10.593
No, that's impossible.

09:10.724 --> 09:13.117
Actually, it is possible.

09:13.204 --> 09:14.858
They've been asked to arrest
and, in some instances,

09:14.989 --> 09:16.381
execute their own kinsmen.

09:16.512 --> 09:18.601
Tends to get people
a little exercised.

09:19.471 --> 09:20.821
[Cardinal Guise]
With the king ill,

09:20.951 --> 09:22.649
if people were to turn
against the Crown,

09:22.779 --> 09:25.521
we would lose control
of the whole country.

09:25.652 --> 09:28.698
We need to act rationally,
unemotionally.

09:28.829 --> 09:31.701
And that is why you must
let us deal with things.

09:33.224 --> 09:34.225
Queen Mother.

09:36.837 --> 09:38.403
What do you think?

09:39.622 --> 09:42.799
I can only think of the health
of my son, our king.

09:44.758 --> 09:47.021
I would hope your uncles
could do the same.

09:48.239 --> 09:49.850
Well said.

09:49.980 --> 09:51.721
[door opens]

09:54.594 --> 09:55.725
How is the king?

09:58.075 --> 10:00.425
I have made
a thorough examination.

10:00.512 --> 10:03.341
There is significant blockage
to both lungs,

10:03.428 --> 10:05.996
as well as extensive
lacerations,

10:06.127 --> 10:08.129
which suggest consumption,

10:08.216 --> 10:10.392
something he
was perhaps born with.

10:12.176 --> 10:12.960
[Cardinal Guise] Will he live?

10:14.831 --> 10:18.269
The king's survival
is extremely unlikely.

10:18.400 --> 10:19.793
[sobs]

10:19.880 --> 10:22.317
[indistinct whispers]

10:22.447 --> 10:25.059
[screaming] No! No!

10:25.189 --> 10:27.322
[whimpering]

10:27.452 --> 10:28.366
Is the strain from the attack?

10:28.497 --> 10:30.238
Is the... the people

10:30.325 --> 10:31.761
responsible for this
will be punished.

10:31.892 --> 10:33.328
[Mary breathing shakily]

10:33.458 --> 10:34.285
They have seen nothing yet.

10:34.416 --> 10:35.939
Do you hear me?

10:36.636 --> 10:38.986
No, we will
soak France in blood

10:39.073 --> 10:40.378
for their treachery!

10:50.606 --> 10:52.390
[knock at door]

10:55.959 --> 10:58.832
-You have visitors.
-Your Majesty.

10:58.962 --> 11:01.878
We've come to offer
our condolences.

11:02.009 --> 11:05.882
I cannot imagine what you're
going through at this time.

11:06.013 --> 11:09.451
Seems as if I am cursed
to outlive those dearest to me.

11:09.581 --> 11:11.583
Now, I know
this is a delicate situation,

11:11.714 --> 11:15.500
Your Majesty,
but the question of succession

11:15.631 --> 11:16.719
needs to be addressed.

11:18.329 --> 11:19.330
What question?

11:21.071 --> 11:22.594
My second son, Charles IX,

11:22.682 --> 11:24.031
will be king
when his brother dies.

11:24.161 --> 11:25.859
Of course,
but due to his youth,

11:25.989 --> 11:27.077
all power must rest
with the regent.

11:28.470 --> 11:30.167
Antoine of Bourbon.

11:30.298 --> 11:31.038
Had it escaped your mind?

11:33.127 --> 11:34.694
I know not very much does.

11:34.781 --> 11:37.000
Initially, the people
will certainly demand

11:37.131 --> 11:40.090
we follow the correct line
of succession.

11:40.221 --> 11:42.702
But once they hear
of the plot against the king,

11:42.832 --> 11:44.225
I'm sure they're
gonna change their mind.

11:46.009 --> 11:47.794
A new regent may be possible,

11:47.924 --> 11:50.927
but the candidate
has to be trusted by the king.

11:51.667 --> 11:54.801
Someone esteemed,
and with experience.

11:59.022 --> 12:00.284
But who?

12:01.851 --> 12:03.853
We were thinking
of Montmorency.

12:07.422 --> 12:08.815
Montmorency
is an honorable man,

12:08.902 --> 12:12.340
but he is hardly in favor.

12:12.470 --> 12:14.603
Up until recently,
he was living in exile.

12:14.734 --> 12:16.518
Yes, but the people like him.

12:16.648 --> 12:18.999
And he represents
a bygone era of stability.

12:19.129 --> 12:20.609
But what of his condition?

12:20.740 --> 12:22.654
He's stable, I'm sure
you'll be pleased to hear.

12:22.785 --> 12:24.961
Yes, expected
to make a full recovery,

12:25.092 --> 12:26.006
God be praised.

12:26.963 --> 12:28.965
A miracle.

12:29.096 --> 12:31.576
We will, however,
need the king's support.

12:33.274 --> 12:35.015
Can we rely on you
to convince him?

12:36.973 --> 12:38.148
Of course.

12:41.195 --> 12:44.372
But to transfer regency,

12:44.502 --> 12:46.330
the regent himself
must sign it over.

12:46.461 --> 12:48.071
Yes, we're very much
aware of that.

12:48.158 --> 12:50.160
My men are searching
the country as we speak.

12:50.247 --> 12:51.727
[Cardinal Guise]
Antoine has proved himself

12:51.858 --> 12:53.555
to be surprisingly
stubborn prey.

12:53.685 --> 12:54.817
Like hunting a mole.

12:58.168 --> 13:00.910
If I may make a suggestion,

13:01.041 --> 13:02.782
Louis has been arrested
for treason.

13:04.131 --> 13:06.481
Offer him clemency

13:06.568 --> 13:08.178
in return for the whereabouts
of his brother.

13:08.309 --> 13:10.137
No.

13:10.224 --> 13:11.747
After the plot
against the king,

13:11.878 --> 13:14.489
Mary will never
go for clemency.

13:14.619 --> 13:17.753
No, but the new regent will.

13:17.884 --> 13:19.755
[tense music plays]

13:19.886 --> 13:23.106
And in the meantime,
she needn't find out.

13:23.193 --> 13:26.327
♪ ♪

13:26.762 --> 13:29.634
You really do have vision.

13:29.809 --> 13:31.941
♪ ♪

13:32.072 --> 13:34.030
Through my grief.

13:34.204 --> 13:36.816
♪ ♪

13:46.695 --> 13:49.132
[whispering]
Our Father, who art in heaven,

13:49.263 --> 13:50.917
give me the strength
to face my enemies.

13:53.441 --> 13:56.009
Thy kingdom come,
thy will be done.

13:57.837 --> 14:00.535
[soft raspy breathing]

14:06.584 --> 14:08.325
This grief feels unbearable,
I know.

14:09.587 --> 14:11.981
But a dying king

14:12.112 --> 14:14.854
makes for
a very dangerous time.

14:14.941 --> 14:17.378
Now is not the moment
to lose your wits.

14:17.508 --> 14:19.380
I have not lost my wits.

14:21.730 --> 14:23.601
I am planning
a cruel and unusual revenge

14:23.688 --> 14:24.994
on all of France's traitors.

14:28.302 --> 14:29.956
You can do that later...

14:33.350 --> 14:34.308
[whispers] When you are regent.

14:36.745 --> 14:38.399
Regent?

14:38.529 --> 14:40.314
[Catherine] It is difficult
to contemplate,

14:40.444 --> 14:44.709
but soon,
your husband will be no more,

14:44.796 --> 14:47.538
and his brother
too young to rule.

14:47.669 --> 14:50.585
A regent is the highest power
in the land.

14:50.715 --> 14:51.586
[devious music plays]

14:51.716 --> 14:53.762
Look ahead, Mary.

14:53.893 --> 14:55.242
Shouldn't that be you?

14:55.416 --> 14:58.071
♪ ♪

14:58.201 --> 15:00.247
Well, if it would help France.

15:00.421 --> 15:02.249
♪ ♪

15:02.379 --> 15:05.252
And it be God's... God's will.

15:05.382 --> 15:06.601
[whispers] I believe it is.

15:08.603 --> 15:10.300
But there are those
who conspire against you.

15:11.345 --> 15:13.086
Who?

15:13.173 --> 15:14.826
I have often wondered
if the Cardinal

15:14.957 --> 15:16.524
is the Catholic
he claims to be.

15:16.654 --> 15:18.308
I am sorry to say

15:18.439 --> 15:20.397
a similar thought
has crossed my mind.

15:20.528 --> 15:22.138
They have confided in me

15:22.269 --> 15:25.272
they wish
to make Montmorency regent

15:25.402 --> 15:27.143
to appease the very men
who attacked our king.

15:28.710 --> 15:30.712
Whereas I, like you,

15:30.842 --> 15:32.757
believe now
is not the time to falter.

15:32.932 --> 15:35.891
♪ ♪

15:36.022 --> 15:38.067
I had not expected
a friend in you, but...

15:41.288 --> 15:42.767
I'm grateful nonetheless.

15:45.118 --> 15:47.207
We are united
in our love for the king.

15:49.122 --> 15:51.515
Let me give you
a piece of advice.

15:51.602 --> 15:53.387
Do not let anyone

15:53.517 --> 15:55.302
stand in the way
of your calling.

15:55.476 --> 15:57.957
♪ ♪

15:58.087 --> 16:02.004
One thing men cannot abide
is a woman in power.

16:02.091 --> 16:03.484
♪ ♪

16:03.571 --> 16:06.400
[dramatic music plays]

16:06.487 --> 16:09.229
♪ ♪

16:13.363 --> 16:15.670
I have to ask you, cousin,

16:15.800 --> 16:17.454
what the fuck
were you thinking?

16:17.541 --> 16:19.326
I told you,

16:19.456 --> 16:21.502
I was there to prevent
an attack on the king.

16:21.632 --> 16:23.199
That you knew about because...

16:23.330 --> 16:25.810
I told you, I'd heard rumor.

16:25.897 --> 16:27.725
I thought it was my duty
to intervene.

16:27.856 --> 16:30.815
I am but a loyal servant
of the Crown.

16:30.946 --> 16:33.296
Fucked is what you are.

16:33.427 --> 16:35.646
Mary's gonna cut off
your fat head.

16:35.733 --> 16:37.692
-She wouldn't dare.
-Oh, she would.

16:37.779 --> 16:39.172
Well, then there'll be
a civil war.

16:39.259 --> 16:41.130
A holy war, if she's got
anything to do with it.

16:41.261 --> 16:42.914
She'll love that.

16:43.002 --> 16:47.136
Well, if she cuts off my head,
yours will be next.

16:47.267 --> 16:48.485
Mark my words.

16:56.624 --> 16:58.365
Ah.

16:58.495 --> 16:59.888
Already crossed your mind,
has it?

17:01.368 --> 17:02.673
That's the thing about zealots.

17:03.892 --> 17:04.980
Nothing's ever enough.

17:06.764 --> 17:09.376
-Oh, God.
-What?

17:09.506 --> 17:11.465
Come on, it's not that bad.

17:11.552 --> 17:12.814
That's what you think,
because you haven't

17:12.944 --> 17:14.685
been through
what I've been through.

17:14.816 --> 17:17.688
Exiled, unemployed,

17:17.819 --> 17:20.300
separated from the only person
you've ever trusted,

17:20.430 --> 17:21.997
burdened with a truth
that nobody'd believe,

17:22.128 --> 17:24.217
because in this game we play,

17:24.304 --> 17:27.176
you sound like a fucking liar
whether you are or not,

17:27.307 --> 17:28.221
and finally...

17:31.267 --> 17:32.616
...sentenced to death.

17:34.705 --> 17:35.793
We can avoid all that.

17:37.186 --> 17:39.580
Hold on, hold on.

17:41.538 --> 17:42.800
What is this truth
you speak of?

17:44.846 --> 17:47.153
You wouldn't believe me,
but trust me when I say...

17:49.329 --> 17:51.635
...you have a serpent
in your midst.

17:51.766 --> 17:53.115
We know.

17:53.202 --> 17:54.421
Mary.

17:54.508 --> 17:55.813
That's why we're here.

17:55.944 --> 17:56.901
You don't have
the faintest idea

17:57.032 --> 17:58.164
what's going on, do you?

17:58.294 --> 17:59.817
[Cardinal Guise] Listen to me.

17:59.948 --> 18:02.646
All you have to do
is tell us where Antoine is,

18:02.777 --> 18:04.735
and you will be pardoned.

18:04.866 --> 18:09.305
No, you listen to me,
you fucking idiot.

18:09.436 --> 18:11.786
If I knew
where the fuck Antoine was,

18:11.916 --> 18:14.049
I would tell you, but I don't.

18:14.180 --> 18:16.965
[somber music plays]

18:17.139 --> 18:18.619
♪ ♪

18:18.749 --> 18:20.099
I really don't.

18:20.273 --> 18:22.144
♪ ♪

18:22.275 --> 18:24.929
I wish I did,
because I miss him.

18:25.104 --> 18:26.583
♪ ♪

18:26.714 --> 18:29.847
I miss my big brother...

18:29.978 --> 18:31.284
twat that he is.

18:31.458 --> 18:34.243
♪ ♪

18:37.551 --> 18:39.770
I won't do it.

18:39.901 --> 18:40.989
Why should I?

18:42.164 --> 18:43.992
You've done it before.

18:44.123 --> 18:46.473
An apple filled with poison
I never forced anyone to eat

18:46.603 --> 18:48.388
is an entirely different thing.

18:48.518 --> 18:50.129
[tense music plays]

18:50.259 --> 18:51.869
He's half dead already.

18:52.000 --> 18:55.308
And besides which, if he lives,

18:55.438 --> 18:57.353
it will mean our destruction.

18:57.484 --> 18:58.485
You should have thought of that
before you stabbed him.

18:58.659 --> 19:01.357
♪ ♪

19:02.750 --> 19:04.534
This is not a request.

19:04.708 --> 19:06.754
♪ ♪

19:06.884 --> 19:10.801
If you fail,
don't bother coming back.

19:10.975 --> 19:13.717
♪ ♪

19:19.636 --> 19:21.203
I win again.

19:21.334 --> 19:23.031
And without any strategy
or skill.

19:24.511 --> 19:25.729
How do you do it?

19:25.860 --> 19:27.949
Pure luck.

19:28.079 --> 19:29.646
It's just always been my way.

19:29.777 --> 19:32.127
Drives Louis mad.

19:32.258 --> 19:34.085
[door clanks, creaks]

19:36.392 --> 19:37.393
Oh.

19:41.832 --> 19:44.095
I see Aabis has been
taking very good care of you.

19:44.226 --> 19:45.836
Well, this isn't

19:45.967 --> 19:48.361
the most salubrious
accommodation I've been in.

19:48.491 --> 19:49.927
Well, I'm sure
Louis would prefer this

19:50.058 --> 19:51.799
to where he finds himself.

19:51.886 --> 19:53.235
How is he?

19:53.366 --> 19:54.541
As well as one could imagine,

19:54.628 --> 19:55.281
being in a dungeon.

19:56.934 --> 19:58.109
Would you give us
a moment, please?

20:00.677 --> 20:02.201
[chickens clucking]

20:07.771 --> 20:08.859
We have business to discuss.

20:08.946 --> 20:10.818
Indeed, we do.

20:10.948 --> 20:13.342
I could be
a bit more comfortable.

20:13.473 --> 20:16.127
My understanding
is that confit de canard

20:16.258 --> 20:17.781
is the specialty
of this region,

20:17.912 --> 20:20.349
which, along with
a nice chilled Burgundy,

20:20.436 --> 20:22.221
would ease my pain somewhat.

20:24.571 --> 20:27.835
Indeed, of course.

20:27.965 --> 20:30.316
And you shall have
all of that and more...

20:33.449 --> 20:34.320
...as soon as you sign this.

20:46.201 --> 20:47.942
Relinquish my regency?

20:49.639 --> 20:50.640
To you?

20:52.425 --> 20:53.295
Why would I do that?

20:56.777 --> 20:59.258
Because, Antoine,

20:59.388 --> 21:01.390
your brother has been
imprisoned for treason...

21:03.392 --> 21:05.873
...and if you don't,
he'll be executed.

21:09.224 --> 21:10.269
No.

21:13.097 --> 21:14.142
What do you mean, no?

21:14.273 --> 21:16.536
I mean no.

21:16.666 --> 21:18.973
My brother told me never
to sign away my regency again,

21:19.060 --> 21:20.496
and I won't.

21:21.802 --> 21:23.325
But his life is in danger.

21:23.456 --> 21:25.371
What proof do I have of that?

21:25.501 --> 21:27.590
Louis is clever.

21:27.721 --> 21:29.679
Always has been.

21:29.810 --> 21:31.464
How do I know he didn't
evade the king's men,

21:31.594 --> 21:33.683
and you're lying about him
being held captive?

21:33.814 --> 21:35.903
Wouldn't be the first time
you've lied about something.

21:36.033 --> 21:38.471
You hoodwinked us into this
whole fucking kidnapping thing

21:38.601 --> 21:40.951
in the first place, against
Louis' better instincts,

21:41.082 --> 21:45.652
I might add,
and if he is imprisoned,

21:45.739 --> 21:47.784
the only thing
keeping him alive

21:47.871 --> 21:51.919
is the fact that I haven't
signed away my regency.

21:52.049 --> 21:53.790
[tense music plays]

21:53.921 --> 21:55.879
So in the words
of my dear grandmother,

21:56.010 --> 21:57.664
get fucked.

21:57.838 --> 22:00.319
♪ ♪

22:05.715 --> 22:07.369
You said you'd help me.

22:07.456 --> 22:08.718
Now is not the time, Aabis.

22:08.849 --> 22:10.503
[Aabis] Then when?

22:10.633 --> 22:12.635
The situation
at the moment is very delicate.

22:12.722 --> 22:14.898
I cannot be seen intervening
on behalf of a Protestant boy.

22:14.985 --> 22:16.813
He's not a fucking Protestant.

22:19.555 --> 22:21.209
And he won't survive
much longer in there.

22:22.384 --> 22:24.517
Tell me,

22:24.647 --> 22:25.822
what is the fate of a young boy

22:25.953 --> 22:27.433
when the fate of a nation
hangs in the balance?

22:29.522 --> 22:31.088
It is everything.

22:32.786 --> 22:33.874
Well, I'm afraid
I don't have time

22:33.961 --> 22:35.005
for such sentimentality.

22:37.138 --> 22:38.008
I'll see to your friend
when I'm able.

22:42.361 --> 22:46.016
You finally reached
for the throne for yourself.

22:46.147 --> 22:48.192
I just don't want
my son to suffer.

23:02.772 --> 23:06.820
It contains an opiate
from the East.

23:11.390 --> 23:13.479
With enough,
he will feel no pain.

23:16.133 --> 23:18.266
But in his condition,
it will shorten his days.

23:18.397 --> 23:20.921
[wind chimes clinking]

23:23.140 --> 23:24.751
His days are done already.

23:29.364 --> 23:32.498
He was marked
for an early grave since birth.

23:32.628 --> 23:33.368
I pray I'm not the reason.

23:33.499 --> 23:34.630
Do not falter.

23:36.589 --> 23:37.764
We are close.

23:39.548 --> 23:41.202
We?

23:41.332 --> 23:43.683
[tense music plays]

23:43.813 --> 23:45.772
I saw this in you
the first day we met.

23:45.946 --> 23:48.688
♪ ♪

24:02.484 --> 24:05.313
[suspenseful music plays]

24:05.487 --> 24:08.229
♪ ♪

24:41.871 --> 24:42.916
[guard] Where do you think
you're going?

24:44.831 --> 24:47.311
I'm Sister Grace

24:47.442 --> 24:49.270
of the Sacred Order
of the Diminutives,

24:49.400 --> 24:50.880
here to tend to the sick.

24:51.011 --> 24:53.230
Order of the Diminutives.

24:53.361 --> 24:54.580
Is that some kind of joke?

24:54.710 --> 24:56.756
You think I'd make that up?

24:56.886 --> 24:58.322
I'm here to wash
and change the patient.

24:58.497 --> 25:00.237
♪ ♪

25:00.368 --> 25:01.978
Go on, then.

25:02.152 --> 25:04.198
♪ ♪

25:04.328 --> 25:05.895
You want to watch?

25:05.982 --> 25:07.418
I mean, I won't judge
if that's your thing,

25:07.506 --> 25:09.420
but according to the Bible,
God certainly will.

25:09.508 --> 25:12.293
♪ ♪

25:14.338 --> 25:15.731
I have to piss anyway.

25:15.905 --> 25:18.604
♪ ♪

25:23.609 --> 25:26.394
[dramatic music plays]

25:26.568 --> 25:29.353
♪ ♪

25:46.327 --> 25:47.807
Mother...

25:50.984 --> 25:52.420
Mother, is that you?

25:52.551 --> 25:53.639
[tense music plays]

25:53.769 --> 25:55.815
Yes, my son.

25:55.945 --> 25:57.251
Sleep now.

25:57.381 --> 25:58.644
[Montmorency sobs]

25:58.774 --> 26:00.471
[Montmorency] It hurts, Mother.

26:00.559 --> 26:02.256
Mother, it hurts.

26:02.386 --> 26:03.997
[Mathilde] It's only a dream.

26:04.127 --> 26:05.607
Sleep now.

26:05.781 --> 26:07.783
♪ ♪

26:07.914 --> 26:10.133
-You sure?
-[breathing shakily]

26:10.220 --> 26:11.570
Doesn't feel like a dream.

26:11.657 --> 26:13.136
Let me live, please.

26:14.703 --> 26:16.052
Your mistress sent you.

26:17.010 --> 26:17.793
[sighs]

26:19.665 --> 26:21.492
Get me past the guards,
and I will let you live.

26:23.407 --> 26:24.104
Have you heard the news?

26:25.932 --> 26:27.890
Montmorency...

26:28.021 --> 26:28.717
he's missing.

26:29.892 --> 26:30.980
Missing?

26:31.111 --> 26:32.634
I fear my uncles
may be involved,

26:32.765 --> 26:34.462
and it is part of their plot
to name him as regent.

26:34.549 --> 26:36.072
My...

26:36.986 --> 26:39.206
My maid saw them visiting Louis
in the dungeons.

26:41.425 --> 26:42.818
Come with me.

26:42.949 --> 26:44.080
There's not a moment to lose.

26:47.214 --> 26:48.650
[Montmorency]
We need to leave here now.

26:48.781 --> 26:50.347
France is no longer safe
for us.

26:50.478 --> 26:51.348
I don't think
that's a good idea.

26:52.828 --> 26:54.221
[Cardinal Guise] No.

26:54.351 --> 26:55.439
I think what you want to do
is stay

26:55.570 --> 26:56.789
and face your
responsibilities to France.

26:56.919 --> 26:57.964
Yeah.

26:58.094 --> 26:59.530
Isn't that right, Edith?

26:59.661 --> 27:02.142
-Don't you speak to her.
-Or what?

27:03.186 --> 27:04.797
Don't look like you're in any
state to be making threats.

27:04.927 --> 27:05.972
[Cardinal Guise]
Here's the thing.

27:06.102 --> 27:07.974
The king's dying,
France needs a new regent,

27:08.104 --> 27:09.540
and Antoine can't do it
'cause everybody knows

27:09.671 --> 27:11.281
about his plot
against the king.

27:12.021 --> 27:13.719
The situation requires
someone neutral,

27:13.806 --> 27:15.242
someone to settle the conflict.

27:16.722 --> 27:17.984
That's you, Montmorency.

27:19.725 --> 27:21.248
But make no mistake,

27:23.163 --> 27:25.513
you will become our regent

27:25.644 --> 27:26.688
if you don't want anything
to happen

27:26.819 --> 27:27.646
to those you care about.

27:27.776 --> 27:30.083
[scoffs]

27:30.213 --> 27:31.954
And you wonder why people
have begun to doubt the Church.

27:32.085 --> 27:33.390
Listen to me.

27:33.521 --> 27:35.566
We are better
than the fucking lunatic

27:35.697 --> 27:37.090
that is in charge right now.

27:37.177 --> 27:38.569
Are you surprised?

27:38.657 --> 27:40.267
Your niece
is what you made her.

27:40.397 --> 27:42.486
Be that as it may,
she's all our problem now.

27:42.617 --> 27:44.401
[chuckles]

27:44.532 --> 27:45.576
You're scared of Mary.
Is that it?

27:47.143 --> 27:49.189
You two are really something.

27:50.581 --> 27:51.713
There's nothing you wouldn't do
in pursuit of power, is there?

27:51.844 --> 27:52.932
Do what they ask.

27:54.498 --> 27:55.543
That's good advice.

27:55.674 --> 27:56.805
Shut the fuck up.

27:58.981 --> 28:00.722
Listen.

28:00.853 --> 28:01.680
I won't let them hurt you.

28:01.810 --> 28:02.637
The people need someone

28:02.768 --> 28:03.943
capable of ruling.

28:06.032 --> 28:07.686
[breathing shakily]

28:07.816 --> 28:09.949
Who else has the stomach
to do what is necessary?

28:18.087 --> 28:18.958
All right.

28:19.088 --> 28:19.785
Good man.

28:21.090 --> 28:23.223
But let me just reiterate,

28:23.353 --> 28:24.703
if the power goes to your head

28:24.833 --> 28:26.487
and you develop some kind
of independent streak--

28:26.574 --> 28:27.706
One thing.

28:29.533 --> 28:32.145
If anything happens to her,
I will kill you.

28:34.451 --> 28:36.018
[Francois] Or die trying.

28:36.149 --> 28:37.324
I don't doubt it.

28:44.810 --> 28:46.725
Don't you understand, hm?

28:48.378 --> 28:49.858
The truth will set you free.

28:49.989 --> 28:52.643
I-I couldn't agree more.

28:52.774 --> 28:53.688
And that- that's why
you have to believe me.

28:53.819 --> 28:55.211
It- it wasn't me.

28:55.342 --> 28:56.909
I was only there
to protect the king.

28:57.039 --> 28:58.388
[stammering]
Catherine, tell- tell her.

28:58.475 --> 29:00.347
Just admit your involvement

29:00.477 --> 29:01.348
and tell us
where to find your brother.

29:01.478 --> 29:04.046
I told you,
I don't know where he is.

29:04.873 --> 29:06.353
Perhaps if we gave him
the proper incentive,

29:06.483 --> 29:07.746
he would tell us the truth.

29:07.876 --> 29:09.051
[tense music plays]

29:09.182 --> 29:10.879
What does that mean?

29:11.053 --> 29:13.795
♪ ♪

29:16.929 --> 29:18.234
Cut off his finger.

29:18.887 --> 29:19.670
-[Louis] What?
-What?

29:21.237 --> 29:22.761
Do not stray
from your path, Mary.

29:22.935 --> 29:25.720
♪ ♪

29:31.726 --> 29:32.771
It was her.

29:32.901 --> 29:34.511
She was behind it.

29:35.121 --> 29:37.384
Mary, I...
I am not your true enemy.

29:37.514 --> 29:38.428
She planned the whole thing.

29:38.515 --> 29:39.560
You have to believe me.

29:39.690 --> 29:41.823
A man would say anything
to save his skin.

29:41.954 --> 29:44.086
You fucking bitch.

29:44.173 --> 29:45.958
Well, I thought you were there
to protect the king.

29:46.045 --> 29:47.263
So which is it?

29:47.394 --> 29:48.699
Are you a loyal servant,

29:48.830 --> 29:50.005
or were you lead astray
by the Queen Mother?

29:50.179 --> 29:53.052
♪ ♪

29:53.182 --> 29:54.314
[whispers] I have one question.

29:54.444 --> 29:55.968
[devious music plays]

29:56.098 --> 29:57.621
Will you hand over your brother

29:57.752 --> 30:00.102
and advise him
to sign the regency over to me?

30:00.233 --> 30:02.235
-You, regent?
-[Mary] Yes.

30:02.322 --> 30:04.237
Did you put her up
to this nonsense?

30:04.367 --> 30:05.412
This is what is best
for France, Louis.

30:05.542 --> 30:06.935
[Louis] Jesus.

30:07.066 --> 30:08.502
Do you even know
what the truth is anymore?

30:08.676 --> 30:10.199
♪ ♪

30:10.330 --> 30:12.767
If you are dedicated
to the cause,

30:12.898 --> 30:14.464
Mary, there is no excess.

30:14.638 --> 30:17.424
♪ ♪

30:17.511 --> 30:20.122
Yes. Guard.

30:20.209 --> 30:21.384
Guard, give me your knife.

30:21.471 --> 30:23.386
No, don't- don't do this.

30:23.517 --> 30:24.823
For the last time,

30:24.953 --> 30:26.607
I ask you to tell me
where Antoine is.

30:26.737 --> 30:29.392
I don't know where he is.

30:29.523 --> 30:30.698
Promise.

30:30.872 --> 30:33.832
♪ ♪

30:33.962 --> 30:35.137
The little one.

30:35.224 --> 30:36.225
You haven't got the guts.

30:36.399 --> 30:37.966
♪ ♪

30:38.097 --> 30:39.576
Hold him down.

30:39.663 --> 30:40.490
[Louis] No, no, no, no. Don't--

30:40.621 --> 30:41.840
[Mary] Hold him down!

30:41.970 --> 30:42.623
Catherine, please,
for the love of God,

30:42.753 --> 30:43.667
don't do this.

30:43.798 --> 30:45.800
Don't do it. Don't--

30:45.931 --> 30:46.757
[Mary] I'm giving you
one last chance.

30:46.888 --> 30:48.934
One last chance.

30:49.021 --> 30:51.806
♪ ♪

30:53.242 --> 30:55.505
Fuck you.

30:55.679 --> 30:57.551
♪ ♪

30:57.681 --> 30:59.292
[Louis screams]

30:59.466 --> 31:02.251
♪ ♪

31:05.646 --> 31:08.257
Ah, fuck, fuck!

31:08.388 --> 31:10.346
[gasping]

31:10.477 --> 31:13.915
[panting] Ah, fuck. Fuck.

31:14.002 --> 31:16.135
Fuck, ah!

31:16.309 --> 31:17.745
♪ ♪

31:17.876 --> 31:19.878
You're fucking mental.

31:20.008 --> 31:22.054
No, I'm not.

31:22.184 --> 31:23.751
I'm just better at this
than you are.

31:23.838 --> 31:25.622
♪ ♪

31:25.753 --> 31:26.972
[whimpering]

31:27.146 --> 31:28.974
♪ ♪

31:29.061 --> 31:31.367
And don't you ever forget it.

31:31.541 --> 31:34.370
♪ ♪

31:34.501 --> 31:35.850
Bring her.

31:35.981 --> 31:37.983
[Louis whimpering]

31:38.157 --> 31:39.810
♪ ♪

31:39.941 --> 31:40.855
[gasps]

31:40.942 --> 31:43.336
♪ ♪

31:43.466 --> 31:45.773
I heard you have
a friend in trouble.

31:45.904 --> 31:47.035
Perhaps I could help.

31:47.166 --> 31:48.341
[shouting in distance]

31:48.428 --> 31:50.517
And in return?

31:50.647 --> 31:52.780
Tell me where to find Antoine.

31:55.609 --> 31:56.871
You said you wanted proof

31:57.002 --> 31:58.612
that your brother
remained in harm's way

31:58.742 --> 32:00.657
if you don't do as I say.

32:03.269 --> 32:04.357
Will that suffice?

32:08.143 --> 32:10.972
Oh, my God,
it's his fucking finger.

32:11.103 --> 32:13.627
And we will cut
piece after piece

32:13.757 --> 32:16.064
after piece of him off...

32:16.151 --> 32:18.588
unless you sign.

32:18.719 --> 32:21.156
He's gonna be
so disappointed in me.

32:23.071 --> 32:24.029
Antoine.

32:24.159 --> 32:26.596
[sighs]

32:31.688 --> 32:32.472
I wouldn't.

32:33.299 --> 32:34.691
Hello, Catherine.

32:36.345 --> 32:37.216
[Cardinal Guise]
This is nice, isn't it?

32:37.346 --> 32:39.479
It's like
a Privy Council meeting,

32:39.566 --> 32:40.741
but with guns.

32:42.961 --> 32:45.572
I think this is the one
you need to sign, cousin.

32:46.877 --> 32:47.922
Montmorency will be regent.

32:50.011 --> 32:53.014
Now, hold on just a minute.

32:53.145 --> 32:54.450
I do have principles, you know.

32:54.581 --> 32:55.712
You don't.

32:55.843 --> 32:56.844
[Antoine] I have been entrusted

32:56.975 --> 32:59.020
to safeguard the honor

32:59.151 --> 33:00.761
of the royal family of France.

33:00.891 --> 33:03.155
I can't just be forced
to sign away the regency

33:03.285 --> 33:04.634
to whomever has the bigger gun.

33:04.765 --> 33:05.896
I don't see why not.

33:07.159 --> 33:08.247
-[gunshot]
-Ah!

33:08.377 --> 33:09.988
[groaning]

33:10.118 --> 33:11.293
What the fuck was that?

33:11.424 --> 33:12.729
[dramatic music plays]

33:12.860 --> 33:14.818
Ah, fuck.

33:15.732 --> 33:17.038
Come what may,
I will be my own man.

33:17.212 --> 33:18.866
♪ ♪

33:18.997 --> 33:20.520
-Sign.
-Stay down!

33:20.650 --> 33:22.174
Stay. Stay down, Francois.

33:22.304 --> 33:24.176
Stay with me, okay?
Just stay with me.

33:24.350 --> 33:25.525
♪ ♪

33:25.655 --> 33:26.526
It's your leg.

33:26.700 --> 33:27.831
♪ ♪

33:27.918 --> 33:29.268
I swear to God, Montmorency,

33:29.355 --> 33:30.530
you mark my words.

33:30.660 --> 33:32.184
You and that girl will pay.

33:32.271 --> 33:34.664
-I swear!
-We'll see about that.

33:34.795 --> 33:37.189
Well... you still doubt
my conviction?

33:37.363 --> 33:40.105
♪ ♪

33:52.030 --> 33:53.379
Good boy.

33:53.509 --> 33:55.424
I'm sure Daddy's proud of you.

33:55.511 --> 33:57.383
Now, I had him
sign over the regency

33:57.513 --> 34:00.560
to someone who's been
overlooked, underestimated,

34:00.690 --> 34:02.431
someone capable
of sacrificing their friends

34:02.562 --> 34:03.737
and plotting with their enemies
to rule France.

34:03.911 --> 34:05.260
♪ ♪

34:05.391 --> 34:08.002
Are you surprised
to see me alive?

34:08.133 --> 34:10.613
I have known you
since you were a child.

34:10.744 --> 34:13.964
I've been watching you.

34:14.095 --> 34:15.705
And either because
of your will to survive

34:15.836 --> 34:19.535
or because you really are
possessed of a black heart,

34:19.666 --> 34:21.972
you are the only one
that can save France

34:22.103 --> 34:23.931
from any of these fucking
idiots when they are in charge.

34:24.062 --> 34:26.803
[solemn music plays]

34:26.977 --> 34:29.763
♪ ♪

34:36.683 --> 34:39.294
All you have to do now
is convince your dying son.

34:40.339 --> 34:41.644
You think you have
the stomach for that?

34:41.731 --> 34:44.517
♪ ♪

34:48.912 --> 34:50.914
Are you okay?

34:51.001 --> 34:52.568
-Did they hurt you?
-I'm all right.

34:52.655 --> 34:55.136
I always knew
I could depend on you.

34:55.267 --> 34:56.442
You've never let me down.

34:56.616 --> 34:59.662
♪ ♪

35:00.098 --> 35:01.447
I said get out!

35:01.534 --> 35:02.796
-[Mary shrieks]
-[tray clatters]

35:05.799 --> 35:08.628
[coughing]

35:17.158 --> 35:18.899
[Mary] I did wrong.
I did wrong.

35:19.029 --> 35:20.814
-[Catherine] Mary, Mary.
-I did wrong.

35:20.944 --> 35:22.903
-I did wrong--the regency.
-Gather yourself.

35:23.033 --> 35:24.818
Tell me, what has happened?

35:24.905 --> 35:26.733
I asked Francis
for the regency,

35:26.863 --> 35:28.430
like you told me to, and...

35:30.476 --> 35:32.217
...he accused me
of all sorts of baseness.

35:32.347 --> 35:33.609
He...

35:33.696 --> 35:35.481
he said...

35:35.568 --> 35:37.700
he said that I wanted him
to be sick,

35:37.831 --> 35:41.487
and worse, that I only ever
loved him for all these years

35:41.617 --> 35:42.923
because of his sickness,
for it meant

35:43.053 --> 35:43.967
that I may one day rule
in his stead,

35:44.098 --> 35:46.535
and he...

35:46.622 --> 35:49.059
he even said
that I had no interest

35:49.190 --> 35:51.410
in performing my wifely duties.

35:51.540 --> 35:52.933
Did he offer you the regency
or not?

35:53.063 --> 35:55.501
No, he refused.

35:55.631 --> 35:57.416
And I begged
for his forgiveness for asking,

35:57.546 --> 36:00.984
but he would grant me
no such peace.

36:01.115 --> 36:03.422
-Oh, Mary, Mary, Mary.
-I... [sobs]

36:03.552 --> 36:05.946
Mary, shh.

36:06.076 --> 36:06.903
Calm yourself.

36:07.034 --> 36:08.253
Yes.

36:08.340 --> 36:11.343
-Go and calm yourself.
-Mm.

36:11.473 --> 36:13.562
I will talk to him,
and I will make this right.

36:13.693 --> 36:17.175
Yes, because he...

36:17.262 --> 36:19.089
he must always know

36:19.220 --> 36:21.179
that I have had
his best interests at heart.

36:21.875 --> 36:23.703
We all do.

36:34.061 --> 36:36.759
[Francis moaning softly]

36:48.989 --> 36:50.469
My son...

37:00.174 --> 37:03.046
Is it true the Bourbons
plotted to kidnap me

37:03.177 --> 37:05.005
and now I must break
the chain of succession?

37:09.183 --> 37:11.359
It is what is best
for the country.

37:12.447 --> 37:14.057
I am sorry I have not
understood your true nature

37:14.188 --> 37:15.842
until now.

37:16.669 --> 37:19.019
But how can you
understand anything now?

37:21.239 --> 37:23.719
They say one sees clearest
when one is closest to death.

37:23.850 --> 37:25.417
Perhaps you won't die.

37:27.157 --> 37:27.636
The doctors
have been wrong before.

37:27.723 --> 37:29.508
No, no.

37:36.210 --> 37:37.167
What's that you've got?

37:52.487 --> 37:54.881
Antoine has agreed to sign
his regency over to you?

37:57.187 --> 37:58.493
Why would he do that?

38:02.105 --> 38:03.672
I persuaded him.

38:05.935 --> 38:08.111
And now you must persuade me.

38:10.810 --> 38:11.767
[sniffs]

38:11.898 --> 38:14.553
[breathing shakily]

38:17.904 --> 38:20.907
You're in great pain,
aren't you?

38:21.037 --> 38:21.908
[Francis] Oh, Mother...

38:23.953 --> 38:25.433
Why does it
have to hurt so much?

38:27.087 --> 38:29.132
I accommodated myself to death.

38:31.004 --> 38:31.831
I always knew
it would come early for me,

38:31.961 --> 38:33.398
but the pain...

38:33.528 --> 38:35.574
I have never felt
anything like the pain.

38:35.704 --> 38:38.446
Shh, shh.

38:42.102 --> 38:45.758
You are the strongest person
I have ever known,

38:45.845 --> 38:48.935
to live with the suffering
that you have endured.

38:49.065 --> 38:50.371
Do you know that?

39:04.951 --> 39:06.605
I have something here...

39:10.478 --> 39:12.393
...that will take
your pain away.

39:17.137 --> 39:18.356
You simply have to take a sip.

39:20.836 --> 39:22.795
But if you do,

39:22.882 --> 39:26.233
it will be an end of this life.

39:26.929 --> 39:29.802
And I fear giving this to you

39:29.932 --> 39:32.326
takes more strength
than I possess.

39:41.466 --> 39:44.469
[tense music plays]

39:44.599 --> 39:48.211
Give it to me, please, Mother.

39:48.298 --> 39:50.953
[somber music plays]

39:51.040 --> 39:52.912
Please give it to me.

39:53.086 --> 39:55.871
♪ ♪

40:12.410 --> 40:13.628
My child...

40:13.802 --> 40:16.588
♪ ♪

40:23.029 --> 40:24.987
And now you must rest.

40:25.161 --> 40:28.034
♪ ♪

40:28.164 --> 40:30.123
Peace awaits.

40:30.210 --> 40:32.995
♪ ♪

40:41.003 --> 40:43.832
[soft dramatic music plays]

40:44.006 --> 40:46.661
♪ ♪

41:03.243 --> 41:07.290
And now I will leave you
to live with your choices.

41:07.465 --> 41:10.206
♪ ♪

41:14.776 --> 41:17.039
Shh, shh, rest.

41:17.170 --> 41:19.215
Just rest.

41:19.346 --> 41:22.436
Shh, rest.

41:22.610 --> 41:25.395
♪ ♪

41:29.269 --> 41:32.054
[somber music plays]

41:32.141 --> 41:34.970
♪ ♪

41:43.718 --> 41:46.373
-[bell tolling]
-[crows cawing]

41:46.504 --> 41:48.680
[Louis panting]

41:53.859 --> 41:56.514
[breathing shakily]

42:03.782 --> 42:06.132
[Louis] Oh, fuck.

42:08.438 --> 42:10.179
Fuck. [grunts]

42:10.310 --> 42:13.226
[panting]

42:26.718 --> 42:29.503
[hyperventilating]

42:33.638 --> 42:34.464
[court messenger]
Hear ye, hear ye!

42:36.336 --> 42:38.251
-Louis of Bourbon...
-Fucking move!

42:38.381 --> 42:39.818
[court messenger]
...Second Prince of the Blood,

42:39.948 --> 42:42.081
is pardoned
for the crime of treason.

42:42.168 --> 42:43.691
What?

42:43.822 --> 42:45.998
[court messenger]
The king is dead.

42:46.128 --> 42:48.740
Long live the new king
by order of the new regent,

42:48.870 --> 42:50.480
Her Majesty Queen Catherine.

42:50.611 --> 42:52.570
[crowd whispering indistinctly]

42:52.657 --> 42:53.571
[exhales sharply]

42:55.398 --> 42:58.010
Then the king is dead,

42:58.140 --> 43:00.142
and my mother-in-law has taken
the regency for herself.

43:02.971 --> 43:04.277
She has made a fool of me.

43:05.539 --> 43:07.106
Fuck off.

43:07.193 --> 43:10.065
[panting]

43:14.243 --> 43:15.680
I shouldn't have
signed away the regency

43:15.767 --> 43:17.246
under any circumstances,
should I?

43:17.377 --> 43:18.683
[tense music plays]

43:18.813 --> 43:20.293
No.

43:20.380 --> 43:22.730
♪ ♪

43:22.861 --> 43:25.298
I... I...

43:25.428 --> 43:28.127
No, I... I will...

43:28.257 --> 43:30.477
I will write to my cousin
Queen Elizabeth in England,

43:30.608 --> 43:32.392
and when she hears that some...

43:32.522 --> 43:34.307
some commoner has stolen
the throne of France,

43:34.437 --> 43:35.177
she will be moved to help me.

43:35.308 --> 43:36.265
I'm sure of it.

43:36.396 --> 43:38.441
I'm sure, despite our...

43:38.572 --> 43:40.835
our differences.

43:40.966 --> 43:44.360
But first, we must all
be united in our task.

43:44.491 --> 43:45.884
The fuck...

43:46.014 --> 43:47.494
Uncle?

43:47.625 --> 43:48.843
Will you back me now?

43:48.930 --> 43:50.976
Yes.

43:51.106 --> 43:53.282
Anything to oppose Catherine.

43:53.413 --> 43:54.544
The Bourbon
Princes of the Blood,

43:54.675 --> 43:55.545
are you with me?

43:55.633 --> 43:58.461
♪ ♪

43:58.592 --> 43:59.941
Am I with you?

44:00.028 --> 44:01.595
Are... are you fucking joking?

44:01.682 --> 44:03.379
My granddaughter has vision.

44:03.510 --> 44:05.991
The sanctity of the rules
of succession are at stake.

44:06.121 --> 44:07.470
Do you really have a choice?

44:07.645 --> 44:10.735
♪ ♪

44:11.257 --> 44:12.911
I'll think about it.

44:13.085 --> 44:15.914
♪ ♪

44:16.044 --> 44:17.393
Let's go.

44:17.480 --> 44:18.656
I'm starving.

44:18.830 --> 44:21.876
♪ ♪

44:22.007 --> 44:23.051
[Antoine] You'll be all right.

44:23.182 --> 44:23.922
[Louis] Oh, no, I'm fucked.

44:24.009 --> 44:25.097
♪ ♪

44:25.227 --> 44:26.054
[Antoine] The finger...

44:26.185 --> 44:26.881
[Louis] Finger's gone.

44:27.055 --> 44:30.015
♪ ♪

44:30.580 --> 44:32.539
[Rahima] Once you were regent,

44:32.626 --> 44:34.889
you moved the court
to Chenonceaux,

44:35.020 --> 44:37.196
where you could keep
a better eye on your enemies.

44:38.066 --> 44:40.025
You only needed
one final piece

44:40.155 --> 44:41.809
to seal your victory
against Mary.

44:43.985 --> 44:45.117
[guard]
I'm sorry, I can't help you.

44:45.247 --> 44:47.075
Please, I just...
I have no one.

44:47.206 --> 44:48.250
And I have nowhere to go.

44:48.381 --> 44:49.599
And I just- I just don't know
what to--

44:49.687 --> 44:51.514
All right, all right,
don't cry.

44:51.645 --> 44:52.994
Let me ask the cook
if she needs another maid.

44:53.125 --> 44:54.169
Thank you.

44:54.343 --> 44:57.085
♪ ♪

45:02.656 --> 45:05.703
Then when you found me...

45:05.833 --> 45:07.835
you didn't waste any time,

45:07.966 --> 45:09.707
because you knew Mary
had sent a letter

45:09.837 --> 45:11.926
to her cousin
Queen Elizabeth of England.

45:12.100 --> 45:13.972
♪ ♪

45:14.102 --> 45:15.713
Make sure this finds its way

45:15.843 --> 45:18.193
to my cousin
Queen Elizabeth of England.

45:18.324 --> 45:20.021
Move posthaste
and let nothing delay you.

45:20.108 --> 45:23.285
♪ ♪

45:23.416 --> 45:25.374
[Rahima]
A letter, I am guessing,

45:25.505 --> 45:27.986
that never found its way
to its recipient,

45:28.116 --> 45:30.423
but could be used
to trick Mary

45:30.553 --> 45:32.294
and get rid of her
once and for all.

45:32.381 --> 45:35.167
♪ ♪

45:41.782 --> 45:43.828
You carry an important message.

45:44.829 --> 45:46.221
How could you know that?

45:46.352 --> 45:48.093
There.

45:48.223 --> 45:49.703
Would you like it?

45:49.834 --> 45:52.532
It's good luck
for your travels.

45:52.662 --> 45:55.404
Do you want me
to tell you your future?

45:55.535 --> 45:58.494
[Rahima] First, you made sure
to win my trust,

45:58.625 --> 46:00.496
so when you asked me,

46:00.627 --> 46:02.672
I would go to Mary's chambers
to search

46:02.803 --> 46:05.763
for evidence of treachery
that did not exist.

46:05.893 --> 46:09.592
And then you made sure
I would despise you,

46:09.723 --> 46:11.812
all to make Mary believe
that the letter

46:11.943 --> 46:14.119
she asked me to steal from you

46:14.249 --> 46:16.991
was an authentic reply
from her cousin.

46:19.211 --> 46:20.865
Though now I know this letter

46:20.995 --> 46:23.258
asking Mary
to return to Scotland

46:23.389 --> 46:26.740
and join forces with Elizabeth
to dethrone you...

46:26.871 --> 46:29.003
is a forgery.

46:29.134 --> 46:30.962
I found the replica
of Queen Elizabeth's seal

46:31.092 --> 46:33.181
in your magician's camp.

46:33.312 --> 46:35.880
The sight of him watching us
on our ride made me suspicious.

46:38.404 --> 46:39.666
You are very clever.

46:41.102 --> 46:42.364
That's why I chose you.

46:44.758 --> 46:46.238
So now that you know...

46:47.848 --> 46:50.938
...are you with me
or against me?

46:53.767 --> 46:56.117
First, I want to know.

46:58.424 --> 47:00.992
You sacrificed
your best friend,

47:01.122 --> 47:03.995
your husband,

47:04.125 --> 47:05.300
your son...

47:07.563 --> 47:08.782
...for power?

47:11.611 --> 47:12.830
No.

47:15.049 --> 47:16.616
For freedom.

47:21.273 --> 47:23.623
In that case,

47:23.753 --> 47:24.842
I am with you.

47:29.585 --> 47:30.760
Here are my terms.

47:37.855 --> 47:38.943
Thought you couldn't read.

47:40.814 --> 47:42.207
There's lots of things
you don't know about me.

47:44.165 --> 47:46.211
A title?

47:46.341 --> 47:47.603
Property?

47:49.910 --> 47:52.652
A little education
is a dangerous thing.

47:52.739 --> 47:54.393
Apparently.

47:57.918 --> 47:59.877
Feels good to be bad,
doesn't it?

48:02.183 --> 48:03.750
Feels better
to get my own back.

48:05.926 --> 48:08.015
Exactly.

48:08.146 --> 48:10.888
[dramatic music plays]

48:11.062 --> 48:13.803
♪ ♪

48:37.262 --> 48:38.263
[exhales sharply]

48:40.178 --> 48:43.616
Mary, Mary, Mary, Mary...

48:43.746 --> 48:45.748
we must prepare
to depart at once.

48:45.879 --> 48:48.882
[laughing shakily]

48:49.013 --> 48:50.797
Oh, my cousin has answered
my call for aid!

48:50.971 --> 48:53.800
♪ ♪

48:56.107 --> 48:57.935
Safe travels.

48:58.065 --> 49:00.372
History will remember you.

49:00.502 --> 49:02.026
Come!

49:02.200 --> 49:04.942
♪ ♪

49:07.988 --> 49:10.164
I wouldn't count on it.

49:10.295 --> 49:13.167
[soft music plays]

49:13.254 --> 49:16.170
♪ ♪

49:16.301 --> 49:18.999
[bells tolling]

49:32.926 --> 49:35.189
I will not let anything
happen to you.

49:36.277 --> 49:37.975
What could happen to me?

49:38.976 --> 49:40.629
Precisely.

49:51.553 --> 49:54.382
[dramatic music plays]

49:54.556 --> 49:57.255
♪ ♪

50:01.955 --> 50:04.784
[indistinct whispers]

50:04.958 --> 50:07.700
♪ ♪

50:31.941 --> 50:34.814
Looks like all is forgiven?

50:34.944 --> 50:37.034
I wouldn't say so.

50:37.121 --> 50:39.906
But I imagine she realizes
she cannot govern

50:40.037 --> 50:42.300
without women like me
on her side.

50:43.431 --> 50:48.001
And I intend to dedicate myself
to her cause.

50:48.088 --> 50:50.482
Well, that's that then.

50:50.612 --> 50:51.961
Checkmate.

50:52.049 --> 50:54.355
On the contrary.

50:54.486 --> 50:56.444
I will spend the rest
of my life getting back at her

50:56.575 --> 50:57.402
for what she did to us.

50:57.576 --> 50:59.230
♪ ♪

50:59.360 --> 51:01.275
But in the meantime,

51:01.406 --> 51:03.756
we shall convince her
we are her closest allies.

51:03.930 --> 51:06.672
♪ ♪

51:12.591 --> 51:15.333
[sweeping music plays]

51:15.507 --> 51:18.249
♪ ♪

51:47.060 --> 51:49.802
[birds calling]

51:53.806 --> 51:55.764
My homeland.

51:55.895 --> 51:58.637
[tense music plays]

51:58.811 --> 51:59.725
♪ ♪

51:59.855 --> 52:02.293
Greetings.

52:02.380 --> 52:05.383
Your queen has returned.

52:05.513 --> 52:08.168
Uh, Queen Mary,
what are you doing here?

52:08.255 --> 52:10.475
My cousin wrote to me saying
that she would help me

52:10.605 --> 52:11.606
in my time of need.

52:11.737 --> 52:14.392
Has she not yet arrived?

52:14.479 --> 52:16.568
Surely, you know
your cousin Elizabeth

52:16.655 --> 52:18.918
would not tolerate
your presence on British soil.

52:19.048 --> 52:20.876
She will see it
as a threat to her rule.

52:20.963 --> 52:22.574
But her letter said that--

52:22.704 --> 52:23.575
-[soldier] Her... her letter?
-Yes.

52:23.662 --> 52:24.793
♪ ♪

52:24.880 --> 52:26.621
If there was such a letter,

52:26.752 --> 52:28.449
I'm... I'm sure
you've been fooled by forgery,

52:28.580 --> 52:29.624
Your Majesty.

52:29.711 --> 52:31.409
♪ ♪

52:31.539 --> 52:35.500
So it was Catherine
who triumphed after all.

52:35.630 --> 52:37.632
And to think, just a week ago,

52:37.763 --> 52:40.722
you had them all
right where you wanted them.

52:40.853 --> 52:42.985
Now she promises
to make tolerance

52:43.116 --> 52:44.900
the new law of the land

52:44.987 --> 52:47.164
and break the treaty
with the Holy Roman emperor.

52:47.338 --> 52:48.513
♪ ♪

52:48.643 --> 52:50.993
No official religion at all.

52:51.124 --> 52:53.561
They will blame you
and your brother.

52:53.692 --> 52:55.215
Mother, when will you shut up?

52:55.302 --> 52:57.435
Isn't it obvious?

52:57.565 --> 52:59.698
When you do something
to shut me up.

52:59.872 --> 53:02.614
♪ ♪

53:10.099 --> 53:11.231
Thank you for your loyalty.

53:11.405 --> 53:13.886
♪ ♪

53:19.196 --> 53:23.025
Keep in mind,
you will only have my loyalty

53:23.112 --> 53:24.679
if you can protect
the people I care about.

53:24.853 --> 53:27.595
♪ ♪

53:35.386 --> 53:37.039
[Catherine] Allow me.

53:37.214 --> 53:39.955
♪ ♪

53:44.656 --> 53:47.441
[dramatic music plays]

53:47.615 --> 53:50.357
♪ ♪

